                  <t:desc type="foundation">Local tradition claims that the church was founded by <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10581Zamika">
                        <t:roleName type="title">ʾabuna</t:roleName> (Za-Mikāʾel) ʾAragāwi</t:persName> (6th cent.), and re-established as monastery by 
                     <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10378Yohanne">Yoḥannǝs IV</t:persName> (r. 1872-1889).</t:desc>
                  <t:ab type="history">Gadām. The comunity includes not more than 10 monks. A church dedicated to <t:persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9162TaklaHa">Takla Haymanot</t:persName>, associated with the monastery, is located in the vicinity.
</t:ab>
